Package randoop.types

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GeneralTypeTuple
    GeneralTypeTuple represents an ordered tuple of type objects.
    TypeArgument
    Created by bjkeller on 4/13/16.
    TypeOrdering

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConcreteArgument
    Created by bjkeller on 4/13/16.
    ConcreteArrayType
    Represents an array type where the element type is a concrete type.
    ConcreteSimpleType
    ConcreteSimpleType represents an atomic concrete type: a primitive type, a non-generic class, an enum, or the rawtype for a generic class.
    ConcreteType
    ConcreteType represents any type that does not have a type variable: a primitive type, a non-generic class, an enum, a parameterized type, or a rawtype.
    ConcreteTypeBound
    Represents a concrete type that occurs as a bound on a type parameter in a class, interface, method or constructor (see JLS 7 section 4.4).
    ConcreteTypes
    Created by bjkeller on 4/8/16.
    ConcreteTypeTuple
    ConcreteTypeTuple represents an ordered tuple of ConcreteType objects, primarily as the input types of #ConcreteOperation objects.
    GeneralType
    Common superclass representing types in Randoop.
    GenericArrayType  
    GenericClassType
    Represents the type of a generic class as can occur in a class declaration, formal parameter or return type.
    GenericType
    Represents generic types that can occur as class declarations, formal parameters or return types.
    GenericTypeBound
    Represents a type bound in which a type variable occurs.
    GenericTypeTuple
    GenericTypeTuple represents a tuple of generic types, primarily as the input to a GenericOperation.
    IntersectionTypeBound
    Represents an intersection type bound on a type parameter in a class, interface, method or constructor (see JLS section 4.4).
    JDKTypes  
    ParameterizedType
    Represents a parameterized type as a generic class instantiated with concrete type arguments.
    PrimitiveTypes  
    RandoopTypeException
    Created by bjkeller on 4/7/16.
    Substitution
    Manages the substitution of concrete types for type variables and wildcards in an instantiation of a generic class as a parameterized type.
    SubtypeOrdering
    Created by bjkeller on 4/11/16.
    SupertypeOrdering
    Created by bjkeller on 4/11/16.
    TypeBound
    Represents a type bound on a type variable occurring as a type parameter in a class, interface, method or constructor.
    TypeNames
    TypeNames provides a pair of static methods to: get string names for classes and primitive types, and get the Class object for a string representing a class or primitive type.
    TypeParameter
    Created by bjkeller on 4/12/16.
    VariableTypeBound
    Created by bjkeller on 4/7/16.
